dcterms:description: The NSL-KDD dataset is an improved version of the KDD-Cup-99 dataset, which consists of a train set and a test set. It contains a total of 125,972 training instances and 22,544 testing instances, with a feature vector of 41 dimensions and labels indicating attack types.
dcterms:title: NSL-KDD

dcterms:description: The NSL-KDD-rand dataset is a constructed dataset derived from the NSL-KDD dataset by combining its training and testing sets, resulting in a different distribution of malicious and benign instances.
dcterms:title: NSL-KDD-rand

dcterms:creator: N. Moustafa
J. Slay
dcterms:description: The UNSW-NB15 dataset was constructed to address issues in the NSL-KDD dataset, containing 2,540,047 observations with a 47-dimensional feature vector and two output attributes indicating attack type and whether the observation is benign or malicious.
dcterms:title: UNSW-NB15
